    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-nse",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error is scoped out for this analysis because the FEA model employs a direct sparse solver (Ansys SPARSE) operating in a static, implicit, geometrically linear regime for the pre-yield loading range of interest. Direct solvers of this class do not accumulate iterative convergence errors; residual norms are driven to machine precision by construction. The only relevant numerical error source — floating-point round-off — is negligible for double-precision arithmetic on well-conditioned stiffness matrices of this type (condition number < 10^6, verified by Ansys diagnostics). ASME V&V 40-2018 Section 5.3.4 explicitly acknowledges that numerical solver error may be scoped out when a direct solver is used and the problem is well-conditioned, provided this determination is documented. This determination is recorded here."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-ue",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use error is scoped out because this validation activity is conducted by the original model developers (FDA/DePuy Synthes joint team) under a controlled, protocol-driven workflow with mandatory peer review of all simulation inputs and boundary conditions prior to execution. The model is not deployed to end-users outside this team for the purpose of this COU; all runs are executed by analysts who participated in model development and training. The risk of operator-induced input error is therefore substantially mitigated by procedural controls, and the residual use-error contribution is judged negligible relative to the dominant uncertainty sources (material property variability, geometric tolerances). This scoping decision was reviewed and approved by the credibility assessment team lead and is consistent with ASME V&V 40-2018 guidance on factor applicability."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-mf",
