        "description": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) constitutive model with Ti-6Al-4V material constants from ASM Handbook validated against uniaxial coupon data; augmented Lagrangian contact at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces; geometric nonlinearity (NLGEOM ON) activated for post-yield regime. Model form justified by literature precedent and confirmed by QoI agreement within acceptance bounds."
      },
      "rationale": "The model form selection — bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V, augmented Lagrangian frictional contact, and large-deformation kinematics — is consistent with published FDA guidance on FEA of orthopedic implants and prior peer-reviewed validation studies. The constitutive model was calibrated against coupon tensile data from the same material lot used for the construct specimens. Gradation 3 is justified by the explicit constitutive model validation and documented contact formulation rationale."
