        "description": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH Biomechanics Lab and DePuy Synthes R&D); constructs assembled from production-representative components; sample traceability documented via lot numbers and CMM inspection reports."
      },
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs from production-representative components were tested across two independent laboratories, providing inter-laboratory reproducibility data. Sample sizes exceed the minimum recommended by ASTM F1717 (N=5). Lot-level traceability and dimensional inspection confirm that test samples are representative of the intended production design. Gradation 3 is achieved by the combination of adequate sample size, two-laboratory testing, and full dimensional traceability."
    },
    {
