        "description": "Testing conducted under a single standardized ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol at room temperature in ambient air; load application rate 25 mm/min; displacement controlled to 40 mm or construct failure, whichever occurs first. Single test condition acknowledged as a limitation; offset rationale provided in decision record."
      },
      "rationale": "Only the ASTM F1717 standard loading condition was tested; physiological loading scenarios (torsion, fatigue, combined loading) were not included in this validation activity. This limits the generalizability of the validation evidence to the compression-bending regime only. The achieved Gradation 2 reflects single-condition testing; the required Gradation 3 is not met. This shortfall is addressed in the decision record offset rationale, which notes that the COU is explicitly scoped to compression-bending prediction and that the single standardized condition is the accepted regulatory submission benchmark."
