      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-cou1-oc-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — E/uval metric and percent difference",
        "description": "Validation metric E/uval (ratio of model error to combined experimental and simulation uncertainty) < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percent difference between FEA mean and experimental mean < 10% for all QoIs. Both criteria must be satisfied simultaneously."
      },
      "rationale": "The output comparison employs the ASME V&V 40 validation metric E/uval computed for each QoI. Combined uncertainty (uval) incorporates experimental measurement uncertainty (±2% from inter-laboratory repeatability study) and simulation numerical uncertainty (GCI-derived). E/uval values of 0.83 (stiffness), 1.12 (yield force), and 0.97 (force at 40 mm) all fall below the 1.96 threshold. Percent differences are 4.2%, 6.8%, and 3.1% respectively, all within the 10% acceptance bound. Gradation 3 is achieved."
